# WNote - Terminal Note Taking Application ğŸ“

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/wnote.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/wnote)
[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/wnote.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/wnote/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

WNote is a beautiful, feature-rich CLI note-taking application that runs entirely in your terminal. Designed for developers and power users who prefer working in the command line, WNote combines simplicity with powerful features like tags, smart attachments with **symlink support**, reminders, templates, and backups.

![WNote Demo](https://via.placeholder.com/800x450.png?text=WNote+Terminal+Application)

## ğŸ¯ Why WNote?

- **ğŸ’¾ Space Efficient**: Symlink mode saves 99% disk space on attachments
- **âš¡ Lightning Fast**: Operations complete in milliseconds
- **ğŸ¨ Beautiful UI**: Rich terminal interface with colors and tables
- **ğŸ”’ Privacy First**: All data stored locally, no cloud sync
- **ğŸ› ï¸ Developer Friendly**: Built with modern Python, easy to extend
- **ğŸ“¦ Zero Config**: Works out of the box, customize when you need

## âœ¨ Features

### Core Features
- âœï¸ **Note Management**: Create, edit, view, update, and delete notes with ease
- ğŸ·ï¸ **Tag System**: Organize notes with customizable colored tags
- ğŸ” **Advanced Search**: Full-text search with relevance scoring and filtering
- ğŸ“Š **Statistics**: Comprehensive statistics and analytics about your notes
- ğŸ¨ **Beautiful UI**: Rich terminal interface powered by the Rich library

### Advanced Features
- ğŸ“ **Smart Attachments**: Three modes for maximum flexibility
  - ğŸ”— **Symlink** (default): Saves 99% space, stays in sync with original
  - ğŸ“„ **Copy**: Safe snapshot, independent of original
  - ğŸ“Œ **Reference**: Path-only, no storage overhead
- â° **Reminders**: Set reminders for important notes with due date tracking
- ğŸ“‹ **Templates**: Create and use note templates for common formats
- ğŸ’¾ **Backup & Restore**: Automatic and manual backup system with compression
- ğŸ“¦ **Archive System**: Archive old notes without deleting them
- ğŸ“¤ **Export**: Export notes to Markdown, HTML, or plain text
- ğŸ”— **Note Linking**: Create relationships between notes (coming soon)
- ğŸ“ **Editor Integration**: Use your favorite text editor (vim, nano, etc.)

